Come on.
She'd never do that.

11:13.306 --> 11:17.442
Oh, yes, she would.
You just don't know her.

11:17.444 --> 11:17.976
I'm her father.

11:17.978 --> 11:21.513
Pops, I'm telling you,
that woman's an evil genius.

11:21.515 --> 11:22.914
Dinner's ready!

11:22.916 --> 11:25.383
I made your favorite,
shrimp parm.

11:25.385 --> 11:26.918
Oh, you made
my favorite?

11:26.920 --> 11:29.187
Well, it doesn't
make up for this.

11:29.189 --> 11:30.288
My goodness!

11:30.290 --> 11:33.391
What happened to
your cool clothes?

11:33.393 --> 11:34.793
You happened.

11:34.795 --> 11:37.195
(WHISPERS)
You happened.

11:37.863 --> 11:39.998
They must've shrunk
when I washed 'em.

11:40.000 --> 11:40.598
It was an accident.

11:40.600 --> 11:44.169
When it comes to
you and the laundry,
there are no accidents.

11:44.171 --> 11:45.704
I always wash new clothes.

11:45.706 --> 11:47.939
You don't know
who tried them on
before you.

11:47.941 --> 11:48.807
Could've been a drifter.

11:48.809 --> 11:50.909
What kind of drifter shops
at the Willow Grove Mall?

11:50.911 --> 11:52.844
Well, what kind of drifter
needs to buy new clothes

11:52.846 --> 11:54.446
when he already has
perfectly good ones?

11:54.448 --> 11:57.515
A drifter with a mom
who drove him to drifting!

11:57.517 --> 12:00.085
The open road was
his only way out!

12:00.087 --> 12:01.119
What's happening?

12:01.121 --> 12:02.320
I'll tell you
what's happening.

12:02.322 --> 12:05.423
You're gonna
wear the clothes
I bought you.

12:05.425 --> 12:06.491
They're perfectly fine.

12:06.493 --> 12:09.994
Holy God!
You did shrink 'em
on purpose!

12:09.996 --> 12:13.298
Okay, there are
some ugly accusations

12:13.300 --> 12:16.301
flying around this house
right now.

12:16.502 --> 12:18.737
Okay, now that
that's been resolved,

12:18.739 --> 12:21.372
I think we all need
to take a deep breath

12:21.374 --> 12:24.142
and put on
our adorable train sweater.

12:24.144 --> 12:26.511
I'll never wear
your train! Ever!

12:26.513 --> 12:29.347
(SCOFFS) Oh, these
are chaffing me,

12:29.349 --> 12:31.282
but I like it!

12:31.284 --> 12:34.419
Bevy, I spent a fortune
on those clothes.

12:34.421 --> 12:35.854
And that store was crazy.

12:35.856 --> 12:39.157
There was a boy
with earrings
in his nipples.

12:39.159 --> 12:40.658
I told you
not to mix in!

12:40.660 --> 12:43.595
But Adam wants
to look stylish.

12:43.597 --> 12:46.998
Oh, I know style.
I am style.

12:47.000 --> 12:49.968
They're just clothes.
Who cares?

12:49.970 --> 12:50.568
I care.

12:50.570 --> 12:55.006
Back-to-school shopping was
one of the last traditions
Adam and I had together.

12:55.008 --> 12:57.175
But now I guess
that's gone, too.

12:57.177 --> 13:00.011
<i>While my mom's plan</i>
<i>to bond with me</i>
<i>had blown up,</i>

13:00.013 --> 13:01.846
<i>my dad's plan</i>
<i>to bond with Erica</i>

13:01.848 --> 13:03.815
<i>was about to make</i>
<i>his head explode.</i>

13:03.817 --> 13:05.917
I mean, if you ask me,
the cop was overreacting.

13:05.919 --> 13:07.752
Like, it was obviously
a flare gun.

13:07.754 --> 13:11.089
So we take off running,
and I lose my shoe
climbing over a fence.

13:11.091 --> 13:15.026
There weren't any cabs,
but luckily this motor home
pulls up.

13:15.028 --> 13:16.194
Buh.
...really nice.

13:16.196 --> 13:17.462
Buh.
What?

13:17.464 --> 13:18.897
Buh! Ugh!

13:18.899 --> 13:20.498
Let's just go back
to silence,

13:20.500 --> 13:22.967
beautiful
daddy-daughter silence.

13:22.969 --> 13:24.869
No more stories!

13:24.871 --> 13:26.271
Why are you freaking out?

13:26.273 --> 13:27.939
I mean, it was all
Lainey's fault.

13:27.941 --> 13:28.673
Oh, how is that?

13:28.675 --> 13:32.410
Every decision you made
in that story
was a terrible one.

13:32.412 --> 13:33.812
You said no judgey-ness.

13:33.814 --> 13:35.613
I'm telling you,
your friend Lainey Lewis...

13:35.615 --> 13:36.948
She is big trouble.

13:36.950 --> 13:39.517
Big trouble!
You're never to
see her again.

13:39.519 --> 13:41.186
She's my best friend!

13:41.188 --> 13:42.387
She is banned!

13:42.389 --> 13:43.121
Banned for life!

13:43.123 --> 13:45.290
Oh, really?
No more talking.

13:45.292 --> 13:46.991
We're gonna roll it out!
Come on!

13:46.993 --> 13:49.093
Ugh! I knew
you couldn't handle it!

13:49.095 --> 13:49.961
Roll it out!
I knew.

13:49.963 --> 13:52.897
Uh, you know what? No.
I am not 10 years old
anymore.

13:52.899 --> 13:57.302
I don't like
roller-skating or unicorns
or slap bracelets.

13:57.304 --> 13:59.771
Don't you take off
the slap bracelet.

13:59.773 --> 14:01.873
That represents friendship.

14:01.875 --> 14:04.509
No, no, don't skate away
from me!

14:04.610 --> 14:06.678
Erica! Ah!

14:06.680 --> 14:09.714
All right.
I'm mergin' here.

14:09.716 --> 14:12.884
I'm mergin'.
Do you see
the sign for merge?

14:12.886 --> 14:14.719
Yield! Yield!

14:14.721 --> 14:17.255
Let me in! Let me in!
(WOMEN SCREAM)

14:17.257 --> 14:19.224
Let me... (SCREAMS)

14:22.661 --> 14:24.529
<i>Daddy-daughter day was</i>
<i>officially a disaster.</i>

14:24.531 --> 14:28.533
<i>Not only had Erica bailed,</i>
<i>but my dad's ankle</i>
<i>was swollen,</i>

14:28.535 --> 14:30.068
<i>and no one could</i>
<i>get him off the rink.</i>

14:30.070 --> 14:32.871
Barry,
I got your message.
Where's your father?

14:32.873 --> 14:33.504
The rink.

14:33.506 --> 14:37.108
Can you please
get him out of here?
He's embarrassing me.

14:37.110 --> 14:39.277
Is that my fanny pack?

14:39.279 --> 14:41.045
Just go!

14:43.515 --> 14:46.818
The merge! What the...
The merge!

14:46.820 --> 14:49.654
Murray. Murray!
The merge!

14:49.656 --> 14:51.289
Oh, my God,
look at your ankle!

14:51.291 --> 14:52.790
It's all swollen
and ballooning.

14:52.792 --> 14:55.693
What are you talking about?
It's the other ankle.

14:55.695 --> 14:56.694
Oh.
Ballooning?

14:56.696 --> 14:58.396
What are you even
doing here?

14:58.398 --> 14:59.230
This was your idea.

14:59.232 --> 15:02.133
You said take Erica out,
so I brought her here.

15:02.135 --> 15:07.505
You brought
your moody teenage daughter
to a roller skating rink?

15:07.640 --> 15:09.307
Mistakes were made.

15:09.309 --> 15:11.576
Uh... Some by me.

15:11.911 --> 15:15.280
I don't know what's going on
with my little peanut.

15:15.282 --> 15:18.116
The kid doesn't even
like unicorns anymore.

15:18.118 --> 15:20.451
She's growing up, Murray.

15:21.854 --> 15:23.988
They all are.

15:34.466 --> 15:37.435
I'd go with
the brown paper bag.

15:37.437 --> 15:40.271
Aw. But Adam
loves Kermie.

15:40.839 --> 15:42.307
You know what?
Your call.

15:42.309 --> 15:43.808
I'm not gonna mix in.

15:43.810 --> 15:46.010
No, you're right.

15:46.378 --> 15:48.079
And, uh, you were right
about the clothes.

15:48.081 --> 15:51.516
Adam is old enough
to pick his own clothes.

15:52.885 --> 15:55.653
But it's all just going by
so fast.

15:56.355 --> 15:57.388
And...

15:57.390 --> 16:00.358
It's hard because every year
he gets older,

16:00.360 --> 16:06.431
and I feel like I'm just
having to say goodbye
to a little boy

16:06.433 --> 16:08.499
I was just gettin' to know.

16:08.501 --> 16:11.469
I went through
the same thing with you.

16:11.804 --> 16:17.442
But you know what made
saying goodbye
to my little girl easier?

16:17.776 --> 16:21.179
I got to see
the woman she became.

16:23.415 --> 16:24.582
(CHUCKLES)

16:24.584 --> 16:29.854
Adam,
get your ass downstairs!
We're going to the mall!

16:30.823 --> 16:32.824
Thanks, Daddy.

16:36.328 --> 16:37.996
Oh, no!
They're closed.

16:37.998 --> 16:40.965
Nothing's closed until
I say it is.

16:41.233 --> 16:43.634
Hey! What are you doing?
We're closing.

16:43.636 --> 16:46.337
My beautiful boy
needs a pair of
acid-washed jeans,

16:46.339 --> 16:48.306
and he needs them
right now.

16:48.308 --> 16:50.408
Can't help you. Sorry.

16:50.410 --> 16:52.443
Sorry?
(CHUCKLES) Oh.

16:52.445 --> 16:54.078
You don't know from sorry.

16:54.080 --> 16:57.415
If you don't let us in,
people will hear about it.

16:57.417 --> 16:58.549
Your co-workers,
your manager.

16:58.551 --> 17:01.285
I will call the CEO
of Jeans Express himself,

17:01.287 --> 17:05.023
and I will have him
dragged out of his important
meeting about jeans

17:05.025 --> 17:07.258
to let him know
that he has an employee

17:07.260 --> 17:09.594
so spiteful,
so petty, so cruel

17:09.596 --> 17:11.863
that she wouldn't let
a yummy boy

17:11.865 --> 17:13.464
shop for his first day
of school.

17:13.466 --> 17:15.199
So I'm gonna ask you
one more time,

17:15.201 --> 17:19.404
and I want you to think
about your answer
very carefully.

17:20.372 --> 17:22.907
Can we please come in?

17:22.909 --> 17:25.543
<i>(COME SAIL AWAY</i> PLAYING)

17:29.081 --> 17:30.181
Thank you.

17:30.183 --> 17:34.085
Also, I have a coupon.
It expired a year ago.

17:34.087 --> 17:35.420
You will honor it.

17:35.422 --> 17:38.489
<i>♪ I'm sailing</i>

17:38.491 --> 17:42.360
MURRAY:
<i>That's it, peanut!</i>
<i>You're doing great!</i>

17:42.362 --> 17:44.395
<i>You're doing it</i>
<i>all by yourself!</i>

17:44.397 --> 17:46.798
<i>♪ Set an open course</i>

17:46.800 --> 17:48.699
<i>♪ For the virgin sea</i>

17:48.701 --> 17:51.035
Yeah,
I remember that day.

17:52.037 --> 17:53.671
Ooh.
Mmm.

17:53.673 --> 17:55.339
I look ridiculous.

17:55.341 --> 17:57.642
You look adorable.

17:57.876 --> 17:59.477
You do.

18:00.345 --> 18:04.515
So today was, uh,
kind of a disaster, huh?

18:04.517 --> 18:07.385
A little, but...

18:07.453 --> 18:10.121
It was fun
busting on Barry.

18:10.123 --> 18:11.622
(LAUGHS) It was.

18:11.624 --> 18:13.858
Oh, my God.
It really was.

18:13.860 --> 18:15.259
Listen.

18:15.461 --> 18:17.962
I may not understand...

18:17.964 --> 18:19.864
Uh, you know, all this.

18:19.866 --> 18:21.332
You know?

18:21.334 --> 18:24.469
But that doesn't mean
I'm not here for you.

18:25.137 --> 18:28.673
Obviously,
go to your mother first.

18:28.675 --> 18:34.078
But if she's not around,
I'm here for you.

18:35.547 --> 18:37.148
Thanks.

18:41.153 --> 18:41.586
(KISSES)

18:41.588 --> 18:43.621
Night, Dad.
Good night, peanut.

18:43.623 --> 18:48.025
<i>♪ Spark my memory</i>

18:48.160 --> 18:51.896
<i>♪ Some happy</i>

18:51.898 --> 18:55.333
<i>♪ Some sad</i>

18:56.502 --> 18:58.703
<i>♪ I think of</i>
<i>childhood friends</i>

18:58.705 --> 19:02.540
Come and get 'em!
Lunches for my honeybunches!

19:02.542 --> 19:05.209
Hey, don't wait up.
I'm studying at
Lainey's tonight.

19:05.211 --> 19:08.779
Studying for what?
Today's the first day
of school.

19:08.781 --> 19:11.849
Don't be a moron!
Get your ass home!

19:11.851 --> 19:12.316
Ugh!

19:12.318 --> 19:13.551
ADULT ADAM:
<i>And just like that,</i>

19:13.553 --> 19:16.254
<i>my dad was back to</i>
<i>talking to Erica.</i>

19:16.256 --> 19:19.657
Look at us!
We're identical twins.

19:19.858 --> 19:22.226
So... How do I look?

19:24.062 --> 19:25.897
Dangerous.

19:28.834 --> 19:32.170
<i>♪ To carry on</i>

19:32.172 --> 19:34.972
<i>We may have outgrown our old</i>
<i>back-to-school traditions,</i>

19:34.974 --> 19:38.209
<i>but thanks to Barry,</i>
<i>we started a new one.</i>

19:38.211 --> 19:41.612
<i>♪ Come sail away,</i>
<i>come sail away</i>

19:41.614 --> 19:44.882
<i>♪ Come sail away</i>
<i>with me, lad</i>

19:44.884 --> 19:48.486
<i>♪ Come sail away,</i>
<i>come sail away</i>

